[[Image:Mssmain.jpg|thumb|right|Sample interface]]

'''Mero sanu sathi''' (literally ''My Small Friend'') is a Nepalese-based [[free and open-source]] package of educational tools. Currently,{{when|date=February 2012}} Mero sanu sathi contains the following tools:
* Barnamala, an alphabet learning tool.
* Dunot, a mathematics learning Tool.
* Kathaearning, a collection of interactive stories.
* Chitrapati, a [[Logo programming language|Logo]]-like IDE for drawing pictures and different geometric shapes.
* Geetm, listening to nursery rhymes.
* Khel, a small interactive and educational games collection.

In 2007, the software was distributed on a number of [[One Laptop Per Child]] computers in the country.

