===Smart Games Puzzle Challenge 2=== {{Video game reviews | PCGUS = 80%<ref name=pcgamerus>{{cite journal | author=Renninger, Lisa H. | journal=[[PC Gamer US]] | url=http://www.pcgamer.com:80/reviews/964.html | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20000301120519/http://www.pcgamer.com/reviews/964.html | archivedate=March 1, 2000 | title=''Smart Games Challenge 2'' | date=February 1998 | deadurl=yes | df= }}</ref> | CGW = {{Rating|5|5}}<ref name=cgw>{{cite journal| author=Ardai, Charles |title=It's Puzzling|date=January 1998 | journal=[[Computer Gaming World]]|issue=162 |page=314 }}</ref> | rev1 = ''[[Computer Games Magazine|Computer Games Strategy Plus]]'' | rev1Score = {{rating|4.5|5}}<ref name=cgm>{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20050319224023/http://www.cdmag.com/articles/009/193/smart_games_review.html |url=http://www.cdmag.com:80/articles/009/193/smart_games_review.html |title=''Smart Games Puzzle Challenge 2'' |author=Yans, Cindy |work=[[Computer Games Magazine|Computer Games Strategy Plus]] |archivedate=March 19, 2005 |date=January 19, 1998 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> }}
In ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', Charles Ardai called ''Smart Games Puzzle Challenge 2'' "brain food of a very high order, caviar for the cranium." He summarized it as "the best bunch of brain-busters ever."<ref name=cgw /> Cindy Yans of ''[[Computer Games Magazine|Computer Games Strategy Plus]]'' wrote, "This is simply the most comprehensive puzzle game around. Hands down."<ref name=cgm />
Writing for ''[[PC Gamer US]]'', Lisa H. Renninger called it "one of the best puzzle collections we’ve seen in a long time", and a vast improvement over its predecessor. She highlighted its "terrific gameplay" and "great puzzle variety".<ref name=pcgamerus />
The editors of ''Computer Gaming World'' named ''Smart Games Puzzle Challenge 2'' the best puzzle game of 1997, and wrote, "Once again, Smart Games goes for substance rather than flash. But with brain-shattering puzzles like these, who needs fluff?"<ref name=cgwpremier1997>{{cite journal | author=Staff | journal=[[Computer Gaming World]] | title=''CGW'' Presents The Best & Worst of 1997 |date=March 1998 | issue=164 | pages=74–77, 80, 84, 88, 89 }}</ref>
PC Game World gave it 80%.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.pcgameworld.com/reviews/s/smartgameschallenge2/index.htm|title=Smart Games Challenge 2 game review - PC Gameworld !!!|date=2001-04-17|access-date=2017-12-30|deadurl=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20010417103404/http://www.pcgameworld.com/reviews/s/smartgameschallenge2/index.htm|archivedate=2001-04-17|df=}}</ref>
===Smart Games Puzzle Challenge 3=== {{Video game reviews | CGW = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=cgw2>{{cite journal| author=Ardai, Charles |title=Still Smart, Still Game|date=March 1999 | journal=[[Computer Gaming World]]|issue=176 |page=203 }}</ref> }}
In ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', Charles Ardai wrote of ''Puzzle Challenge 3'', "Almost three years after they set the puzzle game standard, the folks at Smart Games are still the only ones doing it right." Although he felt that the designers had been forced to rely on "sometimes esoteric" puzzles, since their earlier titles included most of the accessible ones, he argued that "no puzzle lover will leave disappointed." Ardai concluded, "Unlike most series, which tend to start running out of steam by their third installment, ''Smart Games' Puzzle Challenge'' still has all of its original spirit and most of its creative spark."<ref name=cgw2 />
''Puzzle Challenge 3'' was a finalist for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]''{{'}}s award for the best classic game of 1998, although it lost to ''[[You Don't Know Jack (franchise)|You Don't Know Jack: The Ride]]''.<ref name=cgwpremier1998>{{cite journal | author=Staff | journal=[[Computer Gaming World]] | title=''Computer Gaming World''{{'}}s 1999 Premier Awards; ''CGW'' Presents the Best Games of 1998 |date=April 1999 | issue=177 | pages=90, 93, 96–105 }}</ref>
